---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Abhivir Singh">
  <div class="editorial-container">
    <section class="pt-20 pb-12 border-b border-border">
      <h1
        class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4"
      >
        About
      </h1>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-border max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I'm Abhivir. 22. From Faridabad, India. Currently finishing a Master's in
        Computing (AI & ML) at Imperial College London. I transferred from IIT Delhi
        after my first year — got an unconditional offer from Cambridge Trinity and
        Imperial, chose Imperial. Graduating June 2026, then going back to India.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I build things. AI agent platforms, operating systems, compilers, trading engines.
        I've won hackathons, published research on multilingual LLMs, captained a cricket
        team from second division to first, and co-founded the AI Club at Imperial. The
        thread through all of it: I like hard problems and I like shipping.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-6">
        In February 2026, I was at the India AI Summit — sat with Demis Hassabis, met
        Vinod Khosla, Dario Amodei, Alexander Wang. I got there by building a COVID app
        for a Gurdwara, which caught the eye of a government official, which led to
        contributing to India's national nutrition tracker, which led to me asking the
        CEO of the National e-Governance Division if I could come. He said yes. Most people
        never ask.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Now I'm figuring out what to build for India. The problems — in education,
        governance, infrastructure — are massive. AI changes what's possible. I'm looking
        for a co-founder and a first product.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Links -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-16">
      <p class="section-label">Read More</p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <a href="/work" class="editorial-link text-sm block">
          Things I've built &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/highlights" class="editorial-link text-sm block">
          Highlights & proof &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/blog" class="editorial-link text-sm block">
          Writing &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/now" class="editorial-link text-sm block">
          What I'm doing now &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
